tesseract — GPU compute for Go. Zero Python.

Commands:
  pull <model>            Download model from HuggingFace
  models                  List downloaded models
  info <model>            Show model architecture
  bench                   Benchmark your GPU
  gpus                    Detect all GPUs and calibrate
  train                   Train a model
  finetune <model> <data> Fine-tune a model
  quantize <model> [q8|q4] Quantize model weights
  resume <ckpt-dir> <data> Resume training from checkpoint
  merge <model> <adapters> Merge LoRA adapters into base model
  serve <model>           OpenAI-compatible API server
  benchmark <model>       Profile inference speed + memory
  convert gguf <model>    Convert safetensors → GGUF (for Ollama)
  infer <model> "prompt"   Generate text

Global Flags (before command):
  --device <dev>     Target: auto, cuda, metal, cpu (default: auto)
  --precision <mode> Compute: auto, fp32, fp16, int8 (default: auto)
  --out <dir>        Output directory for all artifacts
  --verbose          Show detailed logs
  --helix            Enable helix DNA optimizer
  --needle           Enable needle INT8 kernels

Examples:
  tesseract pull Qwen/Qwen2.5-14B
  tesseract bench
  tesseract infer qwen2-0.5b "The meaning of life is"
  tesseract quantize qwen2.5-14b q8
  tesseract serve qwen2.5-14b
  smoke: --version
